{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857490965,"sessionID":"ses_286a72e99ffefKKmBHNmlIKUHY","part":{"id":"prt_d79594c96001A5DTZxxKVb8KgX","messageID":"msg_d79591d4a001mG9JsqlQPTmCvV","sessionID":"ses_286a72e99ffefKKmBHNmlIKUHY","type":"text","text":"The existing design.md doesn't match the spec in `.sdd_prompt.md`. I need to rewrite it to align with the session-store/spec.md. Let me update the design.md:","time":{"start":1775857490963,"end":1775857490964}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857491117,"sessionID":"ses_286a72e99ffefKKmBHNmlIKUHY","part":{"id":"prt_d795adc16001SAS9i7GOA2EIXq","messageID":"msg_d79591d4a001mG9JsqlQPTmCvV","sessionID":"ses_286a72e99ffefKKmBHNmlIKUHY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-0a2a1390767b44308c67571ea266c426","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md","content":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现 Redis/Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Application Layer                       │\n│                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │\n└────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n                                 │\n                                 v\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Store Interface                            │\n│  Ping / GetSandboxBySessionID / StoreSandbox / UpdateSandbox│\n│  DeleteSandboxBySessionID / ListExpiredSandboxes            │\n│  ListInactiveSandboxes / UpdateSessionLastActivity / Close   │\n└────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n                                 │\n              ┌──────────────────┴──────────────────┐\n              v                                     v\n┌─────────────────────────┐           ┌─────────────────────────┐\n│     redisStore          │           │     valkeyStore         │\n│ (go-redis/v9 Client)    │           │ (valkey-go Client)      │\n└───────────┬─────────────┘           └───────────┬─────────────┘\n            v                                     v\n┌─────────────────────────┐           ┌─────────────────────────┐\n│      Redis Server       │           │     Valkey Server       │\n│   (Single/Cluster)      │           │   (Single/Cluster)      │\n└─────────────────────────┘           └─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Provider Selection\n\n```\n                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                    │   Storage()     │\n                    │  (singleton)    │\n                    └────────┬────────┘\n                             │ initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n                             v\n                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                    │  STORE_TYPE?    │\n                    └────────┬────────┘\n                             │\n              ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐\n              v              v              v\n        \"redis\"         \"valkey\"        other/empty\n              │              │              │\n              v              v              v\n      ┌───────────┐  ┌───────────┐  ┌───────────────┐\n      │redisStore │  │valkeyStore│  │Error: invalid│\n      └───────────┘  └───────────┘  │  provider     │\n                                    └───────────────┘\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Store Interface\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Errors\n\n```go\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n### Provider Type Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n    valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n)\n```\n\n### Redis Implementation\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Valkey Implementation\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Singleton\n\n```go\nvar (\n    initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n    provider      Store\n)\n\nfunc Storage() Store {\n    initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n    return provider\n}\n```\n\n## Redis Key Design\n\n| Key Pattern | Type | Purpose |\n|-------------|------|---------|\n| `session:{id}` | String | JSON document storing SandboxInfo |\n| `session:expiry` | ZSET | Index of sessions by expiry timestamp (score = ExpiresAt Unix) |\n| `session:last_activity` | ZSET | Index of sessions by last activity (score = Unix timestamp) |\n\n### Key Construction\n\n```go\nfunc sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return sessionPrefix + sessionID  // \"session:\" + id\n}\n```\n\n### Document Structure\n\n```\nsession:abc123 = {\n  \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sb-456\",\n  \"sandboxNamespace\": \"default\",\n  \"sandboxName\": \"my-sandbox\",\n  \"name\": \"session-name\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"abc123\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-02T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"entryPoints\": [...],\n  \"userToken\": \"...\",\n  \"serviceAccount\": \"...\",\n  \"serviceAccountName\": \"...\"\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Ping\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n```\n\n- Redis: `PING` command, expects `PONG` response\n- Valkey: `B().Ping().Build()`, expects `PONG` string\n\n### GetSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n- Redis: `GET session:{id}`, `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`\n- Valkey: `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`, `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n\n### StoreSandbox\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n```\n\n**Validation:**\n- Reject nil sandbox\n- Reject zero ExpiresAt\n\n**Atomic Operations (Pipeline/Multi):**\n1. `SETNX session:{id} <json>` - Only create if not exists\n2. `ZADD session:expiry {expiresAtUnix} {sessionID}` - Add to expiry index\n3. `ZADD session:last_activity {nowUnix} {sessionID}` - Add to activity index\n\n**Returns:** Error if any command fails or session already exists\n\n### UpdateSandbox\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n```\n\n- Redis: `SET session:{id} <json> XX` (XX = only if exists)\n- Valkey: `B().Set().Key(key).Value(json).Build()` with existence check\n- Does NOT modify expiry or last_activity ZSETs\n- Returns error if key doesn't exist\n\n### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n```\n\n**Atomic Operations (Pipeline/Multi):**\n1. `DEL session:{id}`\n2. `ZREM session:expiry {sessionID}`\n3. `ZREM session:last_activity {sessionID}`\n\n### ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n- If `limit <= 0`, returns `nil, nil`\n- `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n- Pipeline GET for each session ID\n- Skips missing keys (orphan ZSET members)\n\n### ListInactiveSandboxes\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n- Same logic as ListExpiredSandboxes but uses `session:last_activity` ZSET\n- `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n\n### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n```\n\n**Validation:**\n- Reject empty sessionID\n- If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n\n**Operations:**\n1. Check if `session:{id}` exists\n2. If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n3. `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n\n### Close\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) Close() error\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) Close() error\n```\n\n- Close the underlying client connection\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Custom Errors\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrNotFound              = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n    ErrNilSandbox           = errors.New(\"store: sandbox is nil\")\n    ErrZeroExpiresAt        = errors.New(\"store: expiresAt is required\")\n    ErrEmptySessionID       = errors.New(\"store: sessionID is required\")\n    ErrInvalidProvider      = errors.New(\"store: invalid provider type\")\n    ErrPasswordRequired     = errors.New(\"store: password is required\")\n    ErrKeyNotExists        = errors.New(\"store: key not exists\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Wrapping Examples\n\n```go\n// Redis\nif err == redis.Nil {\n    return ErrNotFound\n}\nreturn fmt.Errorf(\"store: get session %s: %w\", sessionID, err)\n\n// Valkey\nif valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp) {\n    return nil, ErrNotFound\n}\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables (Redis)\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider type (`redis` or `valkey`) |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis address (e.g., `localhost:6379`) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Password (required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n\n### Environment Variables (Valkey)\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Yes | - | Must be `valkey` |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Password (required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`) |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side cache |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single client mode |\n\n### Connection Options\n\n```go\n// Redis\nfunc makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n    addr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n    if addr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    password := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, ErrPasswordRequired\n    }\n    \n    return &redisv9.Options{\n        Addr:     addr,\n        Password: password,\n    }, nil\n}\n\n// Valkey\nfunc makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n    addr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if addr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    password := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, ErrPasswordRequired\n    }\n    \n    opts := &valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: strings.Split(addr, \",\"),\n        Password:    password,\n    }\n    \n    if v, _ := strconv.ParseBool(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\")); v {\n        opts.DisableCache = true\n    }\n    if v, _ := strconv.ParseBool(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\")); v {\n        opts.ForceSingleClient = true\n    }\n    \n    return opts, nil\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```go\n// Using miniredis for Redis tests\nfunc TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    s := miniredis.RunT(t)\n    store := NewRedisStore(s.Addr(), \"\")\n    \n    // Test successful store\n    // Test duplicate store (SETNX behavior)\n    // Test nil sandbox rejection\n    // Test zero ExpiresAt rejection\n}\n\n// Using mocked valkey client for Valkey tests\nfunc TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    // Test with mock client\n}\n```\n\n### Test Categories\n\n| Test Category | Description |\n|--------------|-------------|\n| Ping | Connectivity verification |\n| GetSandboxBySessionID | Found / not found |\n| StoreSandbox | Create new, reject duplicate, validation |\n| UpdateSandbox | Update existing, reject missing |\n| DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Remove all keys and ZSET members |\n| ListExpiredSandboxes | Query by expiry ZSET, handle missing docs |\n| ListInactiveSandboxes | Query by activity ZSET, handle missing docs |\n| UpdateSessionLastActivity | Check existence, update ZSET score |\n| Close | Clean shutdown |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestRedisStore_Integration(t *testing.T) {\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n    }\n    \n    // Use real Redis or miniredis\n    // Verify end-to-end operations\n    // Test pipeline atomicity\n}\n```\n\n### Test Utilities\n\n```go\nfunc setupTestRedis(t *testing.T) *redisStore {\n    mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n    return &redisStore{\n        cli:                  redisv9.NewClient(&redisv9.Options{Addr: mr.Addr()}),\n        sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }\n}\n\nfunc makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{\n        Kind:             types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n        SandboxID:        \"sb-\" + sessionID,\n        SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n        Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n        SessionID:         sessionID,\n        CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n        ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(24 * time.Hour),\n        Status:           \"active\",\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\n  store.go           — Store interface, ErrNotFound, singleton access\n  store_redis.go    — redisStore implementation\n  store_valkey.go   — valkeyStore implementation\n  store_test.go     — Unit tests (using miniredis and mocks)\n  doc.go            — Package documentation\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | latest | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | latest | Logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | local | SandboxInfo type |\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Redis Implementation\n\n1. **Pipeline for Atomicity**: StoreSandbox and DeleteSandboxBySessionID use pipelines to ensure atomic multi-key operations\n2. **MGET for Batch Reads**: ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes can batch GET requests\n3. **Connection Pooling**: go-redis manages connection pooling automatically\n\n### Valkey Implementation\n\n1. **DoMulti for Atomicity**: Similar to Redis pipeline\n2. **Mget for Batch Reads**: Single MGET command for multiple session documents\n3. **Client-Side Cache**: Optional `DisableCache` for memory-sensitive deployments\n\n### Key Locality\n\nFor Valkey cluster deployments, ensure session keys and ZSET keys map to the same slot by using hash tags:\n\n```\nsession:{sessionID}          → uses hash tag\nsession:expiry               → no hash tag needed (single key)\nsession:last_activity        → no hash tag needed (single key)\n```\n\nNote: Current implementation assumes single-node or properly sharded deployment. For multi-node clusters, consider using hash tags for session IDs.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Password Protection**: Password required by default, can be disabled for local development\n2. **TLS Support**: Both go-redis and valkey-go support TLS connections (add via config)\n3. **No Secrets in Logs**: Ensure session data with UserToken is not logged\n\n## Migration Notes\n\nIf migrating from a previous store implementation:\n\n1. Data migration script to convert existing sessions to new JSON format\n2. Rebuild ZSET indexes from existing session data\n3. Run dual-write period during migration window\n\n## References\n\n- AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义 (Store interface)\n- Redis Documentation: https://redis.io/docs/\n- go-redis Documentation: https://redis.uptrace.dev/\n- Valkey-go Documentation: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":60,"character":40},"end":{"line":60,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#omitzero"},"source":"omitzero","message":"Omitempty has no effect on nested struct fields"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md","time":{"start":1775857491041,"end":1775857491115}}}}
